Product Description

Launched by the design house of Chanel in 2002 Chanel Chance by Chanel is classified as a flowery fragrance. This feminine scent posesses a blend of: a refined blend of jasmine and citrus. It is recommended for daytime wear. What is a Tester? A Tester is a perfume with no fancy packaging but with the same exact fragrance at an even better price. They are just like the one used to test the perfume in a department store but supplied in a plain box and often have the word tester printed on the bottle. Sometimes they do not come with a cap or box. These items are great for personal use but may not be great as gifts. Our testers are new unopened and have never been sprayed (Testers and unboxed product are exactly the same as the regular perfume except testers usually come in a plain box--with or without a cap. Unboxed products are the perfume or bath product only without the box.)

Product Description

Coco Mademoiselle by Chanel is a Chypre floral fragrance for women. Coco Mademoiselle was launched in 2001. The nose behind this fragrance is Jacques Polge. Top notes are orange mandarin orange orange blossom and bergamot; middle notes are mimose jasmine turkish rose and ylang-ylang; base notes are tonka bean patchouli opoponax vanilla vetiver and white musk. This perfume is the winner of award FiFi Award Best National Advertising Campaign / TV 2008.
